extern native findFirmwarePatch	// findFirmwarePatch(int index, int nameMaxLength, int name[31 + 1], int* size, int modDate[8 + 1]) -> int : returns 1 if found, returns 0 if no more patches available (which also means next call will refresh the list).

const int FILE_TYPE_COUNT = 4
const int FILE_TYPE_EXE = 0
const int FILE_TYPE_SYS = 1
const int FILE_TYPE_TXT = 2
const int FILE_TYPE_BIN = 3
readonly array FILE_TYPE_STRINGS[FILE_TYPE_COUNT] = {
	"exe", "sys", "txt", "bin"
}

const int FILE_FIELD_NAME = 0
const int FILE_FIELD_TYPE = 1
const int FILE_FIELD_SIZE = 2
const int FILE_FIELD_DATE = 3
const int FILE_FIELD_COUNT = 4

const int MAX_FILE_COUNT = 100
const int MAX_FILE_NAME_LENGTH = 31
const int BUILT_IN_FILE_COUNT = 14
global int fileCount = BUILT_IN_FILE_COUNT

global array FILES[MAX_FILE_COUNT * FILE_FIELD_COUNT] = {
	  "about"	, FILE_TYPE_TXT	, 2		, "11/13/84"
	, "advent"	, FILE_TYPE_EXE	, 91	, " 2/21/78"
	, "bluprint", FILE_TYPE_TXT	, 2 	, " 6/ 5/79"
	, "calc"	, FILE_TYPE_EXE	, 7		, "11/25/77"
	, "chess"	, FILE_TYPE_EXE	, 16	, " 3/ 6/84"
	, "disasm"	, FILE_TYPE_EXE	, 4		, "11/25/77"
	, "fredrik"	, FILE_TYPE_TXT	, 5		, " 7/14/84"
	, "life"	, FILE_TYPE_EXE	, 5		, " 3/12/79"
	, "magnus"	, FILE_TYPE_TXT	, 5		, " 6/22/84"
	, "patch"	, FILE_TYPE_EXE	, 3  	, " 2/18/84"
	, "permut8"	, FILE_TYPE_SYS	, 82	, " 3/ 1/83"
	, "prawnos"	, FILE_TYPE_SYS	, 58	, "10/11/84"
	, "readme"	, FILE_TYPE_TXT	, 2		, "12/14/79"
	, "version"	, FILE_TYPE_TXT	, 1		, "11/13/84"
};
global array FILE_NAMES[MAX_FILE_COUNT * (MAX_FILE_NAME_LENGTH + 1)];
global array FILE_DATES[MAX_FILE_COUNT * 9];

global int filesAreInited = 0;

function strcmp(pointer s0, pointer s1)
returns int d
locals pointer a, pointer b, int c
{
	a = s0;
	b = s1;
	while ((d = (c = (int)*a) - (int)*b) == 0 && c != 0) {
		a = a + 1;
		b = b + 1;
	}
}

function sortFiles()
locals int i, int j, int minJ, pointer minS, pointer s, array temp[FILE_FIELD_COUNT], pointer p0, pointer p1
{
	for (i = 0 to global fileCount - 1) {
		minJ = i;
		minS = (pointer) global FILES[i * FILE_FIELD_COUNT];
		for (j = i + 1 to global fileCount) {
			if ((int) strcmp((s = (pointer) global FILES[j * FILE_FIELD_COUNT + FILE_FIELD_NAME]), minS) < 0) {
				minJ = j;
				minS = s;
			}
		}
		copy (FILE_FIELD_COUNT from (p0 = &global FILES[minJ * FILE_FIELD_COUNT]) to temp);
		copy (FILE_FIELD_COUNT from (p1 = &global FILES[i * FILE_FIELD_COUNT]) to p0);
		copy (FILE_FIELD_COUNT from temp to p1);
	}
}

function initFilesIfNecessary()
locals int index, int size, pointer filePointer, pointer namePointer, pointer datePointer
{
	if (global filesAreInited == 0) {
		assert(global fileCount == BUILT_IN_FILE_COUNT);
		index = 0;
		filePointer = &global FILES[BUILT_IN_FILE_COUNT * FILE_FIELD_COUNT];
		namePointer = global FILE_NAMES;
		datePointer = global FILE_DATES;
		while ((int) findFirmwarePatch(index, 31, namePointer, &size, datePointer) == 1) {
			if (index < MAX_FILE_COUNT) {
				filePointer[FILE_FIELD_NAME] = namePointer;
				filePointer[FILE_FIELD_TYPE] = FILE_TYPE_BIN;
				filePointer[FILE_FIELD_SIZE] = (size + 1023) / 1024;
				filePointer[FILE_FIELD_DATE] = datePointer;
				index = index + 1;
				filePointer = filePointer + FILE_FIELD_COUNT;
				namePointer = namePointer + (MAX_FILE_NAME_LENGTH + 1);
				datePointer = datePointer + 9;
				assert(filePointer < &global FILES[MAX_FILE_COUNT * FILE_FIELD_COUNT]);
				assert(namePointer < &global FILE_NAMES[MAX_FILE_COUNT * (MAX_FILE_NAME_LENGTH + 1)]);
				assert(datePointer < &global FILE_DATES[MAX_FILE_COUNT * 9]);
			}
		}
		global fileCount = BUILT_IN_FILE_COUNT + index;

		sortFiles();

		global filesAreInited = 1;
	}
}

function findFile(pointer s0)
returns int file
{
	initFilesIfNecessary();
	for (file = 0 to global fileCount)
		if ((int)strcmp(s0, global FILES[file * FILE_FIELD_COUNT + FILE_FIELD_NAME]) == 0) goto found;
	file = -1;
found: ;
}

function lower(pointer s)
locals pointer p, int c
{
	p = s;
	while ((c = (int)*p) != 0) {
		if (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') *p = c + ('a' - 'A');
		p = p + 1;
	}
}
